<h2>Behaviour</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Paging.</strong> CSS scroll-snap pages between slides; controls and markers drive <code>scrollIntoView</code> (or the native scroll-button) — no bespoke transform math.</li>
  <li><strong>Accessibility (mandatory).</strong> The rotating region announces the current slide via a live region; prev/next + a slide-picker are exposed; slides form an accessibly-named group.</li>
  <li><strong>Autoplay (opt-in, gated).</strong> Off by default. When on: pauses on hover/focus, honours <code>prefers-reduced-motion</code> (no auto-advance), and exposes a visible pause/play control.</li>
  <li><strong>Motion.</strong> Slide transitions compose the <a href="/intents/motion/">Motion Intent</a>; navigation controls compose the <a href="/intents/navigation/">Navigation Intent</a>.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Boundaries</h2>
<p>
  Equivalent slides, not labelled panels (<a href="/blocks/tabs/">tabs</a>) and not paginated data
  (<a href="/intents/collection-operations/">Collection Operations</a>). A carousel composes Navigation for
  its prev/next + markers but is its own pattern.
</p>
